Lebanese legislators will choose a successor to Omar Karami, whose government resigned Monday amid mass protests two weeks after former Prime Minister Rafik Hariri was assassinated.
Saad Rafik Hariri will assume the historic responsibility and leadership of all national and political affairs.
Hariri's sister Bahiya is a member of parliament.
The announcement came ahead of parliamentary elections that should take place by the end of May.
Meanwhile, opposition groups, which accuse Syria of being behind Hariri's death, called for popular protests to continue until Syria withdraws its troops from Lebanon.
